Ingredients:🩷
Save for later📌

	•	1 tablespoon beetroot juice (freshly extracted)
	•	1 teaspoon sugar (fine granules work best)
	•	1 teaspoon honey
	•	1 teaspoon coconut oil

Steps to Prepare:
	1.	Mix the beetroot juice, sugar, honey, and coconut oil in a small bowl to form a paste.
	2.	Apply the mixture to your lips and gently scrub in circular motions for 2-3 minutes.
	3.	Leave it on for another 5 minutes to let the beetroot’s natural tint and nutrients work.
	4.	Rinse off with lukewarm water and apply a lip balm for hydration.

Use:
	•	Use this scrub 2-3 times a week for soft, naturally pink lips.
	•	Store in an airtight container for up to 5 days in the refrigerator.

	2.	Raw Milk – 2 tbsp
(Hydrates, brightens, and gently exfoliates)
	3.	Honey – 1 tsp
(Anti-bacterial, moisturizes, and calms irritation)
	4.	A pinch of Turmeric (Optional, for acne-prone skin)
(Fights pimples and reduces pigmentation)

⸻

How to Use:
	•	Mix all ingredients into a smooth paste.
	•	Apply evenly on cleansed face.
	•	Leave for 15–20 mins, rinse with lukewarm water.
	•	Use 2–3 times a week for best results.
